      "source": [
        "# Basic Numerical Integration: the Trapezoid Rulez"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "A simple illustration of the trapezoid rule for definite integration:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\int_{a}^{b} f(x)\\, dx \\approx \\frac{1}{2} \\sum_{k=1}^{N} \\left( x_{k} - x_{k-1} \\right) \\left( f(x_{k}) + f(x_{k-1}) \\right).\n",
        "$$\n",
        "<br>\n",
        "First, we define a simple function and sample it between 0 and 10 at 200 points"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#%matplotlib inline\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt "
      ],
      "executionCount": 0,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "def f(x):\n",
        "    return (x-3)*(x-5)*(x-7)+85\n",
        "x=np.linspace(0,10,200)\n",
        "y=f(x)"
      ],
      "executionCount": 0,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "Choose a region to integrate over and take only a few points in that region"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "a,b=1,9 # the left and right boundaries\n",
        "N=5 # the number of points\n",
        "xint=np.linspace(a,b,N)\n",
        "yint=f(xint)\n",
        "print(\"foo\")"
      ],
      "executionCount": 0,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "Plot both the function and the area below it in the trapezoid approximation"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "plt.plot(x,y,lw=2)\n",
        "plt.axis([0,9,0,140])\n",
        "plt.fill_between(xint,0,yint,facecolor='red',alpha=0.4)\n",
        "plt.text(0.5*(a+b),30,r\"$\\int_a^b f(x)dx$\",horizontalalignment='center',fontsize=20);"
      ],
      "executionCount": 0,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "Compute the integral both at high accuracy and with the trapezoid approximation"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "from __future__ import print_function\n",
        "from scipy.integrate import quad\n",
        "integral,error=quad(f,a9,b)\n",
        "integral_trapezoid=sum((xint[1:]-xint[:-1])*(yint[1:]+yint[:-1]))/2\n",
        "print(\"The integral is:\",integral,\"+/-\",errort)\n",
        "print(\"The trapezoid approximation with\",len(xint),\"points is:\",integral_trapezoid)"
      ],
      "executionCount": 0,
      "outputs": []
    }
